# VPC endpoints & PrivateLink

Reach AWS services **privately** — no IGW / NAT / VPN. (NAT costs + regulated traffic can't leave AWS.)

## Two endpoint types

- **Gateway Endpoint** — **S3 & DynamoDB only**, **free**, adds a **route** (prefix list)
- **Interface Endpoint** (PrivateLink) — **most services**, an **ENI + private IP**, per-hr + per-GB, optional **private DNS**

**Rule:** Gateway for S3/DynamoDB (free) · Interface for everything else.

## PrivateLink — expose *your* service

Provider puts an **NLB** + **Endpoint Service**; consumers make an Interface Endpoint → private backbone traffic. For **SaaS vendors** + **cross-account microservices** (no peering, no CIDR clash).
